title.narrative: Infant and Young Child Feeding (IYCF) practices and micronutrient supplementation are improved

description.narrative: During 2021 and the COVID-19 pandemic, UNICEF SCO has continued to reach the most vulnerable children under 5 years and pregnant and lactating women with essential and life-saving nutrition services. This includes 1,296,753 children and women screened for acute malnutrition and 6,323 children admitted for the treatment for severe acute malnutrition (SAM). To prevent malnutrition, 547,292 children under 5 (273,403 boys, 273,889 girls) and 265,636 pregnant and lactating women were provided with multiple micronutrient supplementation and 1,127,242 caregivers including pregnant and lactating women were counselled on optimal IYCF practices. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
